# Commit preferences

When the user asks to commit (e.g. "commit", "commit this", "commit with my usual style"):

1. Read the project root file **AGENTS.md**.
2. If it contains a **Commits** (or similar) section with preferences, follow those for the commit message and any related steps.
3. If there are no commit preferences in AGENTS.md, use a clear, conventional commit message that describes the staged changes.
